ance to it. The areas covered include: sexuality and identity; psychological dependency on technology; libertarian education; religion and spirituality; protest tactics; mental health and artistic expression; and the ongoing 'metaphorical wars' against drugs and terror. This collection epitomises the rich diversity that exists within contemporary anarchism as well as demonstrating its ongoing relevance as a sociological tool.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAnarchism. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aaddiction.  aanarchist practice.  aanarchist theory.  aanarcho-communism.  aanti-capitalist movements.  aanti-civilisational anarchist critique.  aanti-technological anarchist critique.  aecological anarchism.  aeducation.  amental health.  aphilosophical strategies.  apolitical philosophy.  apoststructuralist.  apsychological critique.  asexuality.  asocial anarchism.  asocialisation.1 aBowen, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBowen, James, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCraig, Colin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoaman, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGore, Joanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGribble, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeckert, Jamie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMillett, Steve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorland, Dave, econtributor.